pullRequest.title: [Auth] Save audit details with features and observations
pullRequest.bodyText:
Introduces AuditInfo* across all persistence layers. This include the user making feature or observation mutations, the client timestamp, and the server timestamp once synced.
User id is stored with mutations in local db.
User is fetched from local store when syncing mutations to server.
User email, display name, and id are replicated across observations and features for simplicity and to reduce no. of server queries.
Removes "Anonymous" as a concept in code; user is required for most options, and is generally non-null, except in data objects for data integrity robustness.

Fixes #79.
